<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="834" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.85/358</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SFJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-25T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 21, 8 p.m. You may say to the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            that this Government has the matter of the purchase and change of flag
                            of the <hi rend="italic">Bahia Blanca</hi> under careful consideration
                            and desires to be informed as to the routes proposed for her to follow
                            in Government or any other service. You may intimate that you believe
                            that this Government would be inclined to recognize transfer provided
                            that voyages are satisfactory to this Government and provided Argentine
                            Government will give proper assurance that the vessel carries no crew,
                            officers, or passengers of enemy nationality.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>